com.github.mikephil.charting.data

Class Entry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.mikephil.charting.data.Entry
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BarEntry, BubbleEntry, CandleEntry

    public class Entry
extends java.lang.Object
    Class representing one entry in the chart. Might contain multiple values. Might only contain a single yValue depending on the used constructor.
    Author:
    Philipp Jahoda

      • Entry

        public Entry(float val,
     int xIndex)
        A Entry represents one single entry in the chart.
        Parameters:
        val - the yPx yValue (the actual yValue of the entry)
        xIndex - the corresponding index in the xPx yValue array (index on the xPx-axis of the chart, must NOT be higher than the length of the xPx-values String array)

      • Entry

        public Entry(float val,
     int xIndex,
     java.lang.Object data)
        A Entry represents one single entry in the chart.
        Parameters:
        val - the yPx yValue (the actual yValue of the entry)
        xIndex - the corresponding index in the xPx yValue array (index on the xPx-axis of the chart, must NOT be higher than the length of the xPx-values String array)
        data - Spot for additional data this Entry represents.
